Class HugeHashSet<E>

  • java.lang.Object

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of elements
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.Set<E>

    public class HugeHashSet<E>
extends AbstractHugeHashSet<E>
    A Set that stores elements in a MemoryManager.

    The implementation mimics a HashSet.

    Access to single elements is O(1).

    In order to store the keys and values in the MemoryManager they must be serialized and deserialized to read them. This is done by a Converter which can be specified in the HugeHashSet.Builder. The default Converter can handle instances of all serializable classes.
